  "prompt": "What is the most used word in Malayalam?",
  "response": "The most commonly used word in Malayalam, like in many languages, can vary depending on context, but one of the most frequently used words is \"\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d\" (ennu). This word has multiple uses, including as a conjunction meaning \"that\" or \"said,\" and as a way to indicate time or date, similar to \"on\" or \"at.\"\n\nFor example:\n- \u0d05\u0d35\u0d7b \u0d2a\u0d31\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e\u0d41 \u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d (avan paranju ennu) - He said that.\n- \u0d1e\u0d3e\u0d7b \u0d35\u0d30\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d (njan varum ennu) - I will come on that day.\n\nThis versatility makes \"\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d\" a very common word in everyday Malayalam conversations.",
